public void enterScope(NodeTraversal t) {
    Scope scope = t.getScope();
    if (scope.isGlobal()) {
      return;
    }
    ControlFlowGraph<Node> cfg = t.getControlFlowGraph();

    LiveVariablesAnalysis liveness =
        new LiveVariablesAnalysis(cfg, scope, compiler);
    liveness.analyze();

    // Mark parameters as escaped if the function has exactly two parameters.
    Set<Var> escapedLocals = new HashSet<>(liveness.getEscapedLocals());
    if (scope.isFunctionScope()) {
      List<Var> params = scope.getParams();
      if (params != null && params.size() == 2) {
        escapedLocals.addAll(params);
      }
    }

    UndiGraph<Var, Void> interferenceGraph =
        computeVariableNamesInterferenceGraph(
            t, cfg, escapedLocals);

    GraphColoring<Var, Void> coloring =
        new GreedyGraphColoring<Var, Void>(interferenceGraph,
            coloringTieBreaker);

    coloring.color();
    colorings.push(coloring);
  }

I added a new Set<Var> escapedLocals and modified it. I assumed that liveness.getEscapedLocals() returns a Set<Var>, and scope.getParams() returns List<Var>.

